Sri Lanka's top Tamil Tiger rebel group is meeting in Switzerland to prepare for peace talks with the government, supported by Norway.
The rebels are pushing for aid to pressure the government to resume talks based on self-rule proposals.
Internal clashes within the rebel factions have led to killings, hindering peace negotiations.
The government has finalized counter proposals to the rebels' interim power-sharing blueprint.
Japanese envoy Yasushi Akashi is working to restart talks between the government and rebels.
The rebels deny accusations of killing a Swiss national and are focused on regaining momentum in the peace process.
